      </xs:documentation>
    </xs:annotation>
    <xs:choice>
      <xs:element name="ToleranceValueSelector"
                  type="CylindricityToleranceSelectorType">
        <xs:annotation>
          <xs:documentation>
            The ToleranceValueSelector element is the choice of a
            simple cylindricity tolerance with an optional dual value
            and an optional per-unit tolerance.
          </xs:documentation>
        </xs:annotation>
      </xs:element>
      <xs:element name="CylindricityPerUnit"
                  type="CylindricityPerUnitType">
        <xs:annotation>
          <xs:documentation>
            The CylindricityPerUnit element gives the definition of
            a cylindricity tolerance zone on a per-unit basis.
            Unlike for straightness and flatness there is no section
            in ANSI Y14.5 which explicitly deals with this concept.
          </xs:documentation>
        </xs:annotation>
      </xs:element>
    </xs:choice>
  </xs:complexType>

